results.title: The Crimelord of New York!
results.description: Eduardo Lobo attacks the Arranger, prompting him to ask for Spider-Man for aid in the coming gang war; the Chameleon proposes an alliance with Hammerhead

results.title: Chains
results.description: As he attempts to escape from the Chameleon, J. Jonah Jameson reflects on his first job with the Daily Bugle

results.title: Wolves in the Night
results.description: Spider-Man learns that the Lobo brothers plan an assault on the Kingpin's headquarters

results.title: The Wolves of War
results.description: The Lobo brothers assault the Kingpin's headquarters; Spider-Man confronts the Chameleon and rescues J. Jonah Jameson; Peter and Mary Jane learn that Kristy is bulimic

results.title: Showdown
results.description: The gang war comes to a bloody conclusion

results.title: Skin-Deep
results.description: Spider-Man and Rocket Racer fight racism on the Empire State University campus; J. Jonah Jameson learns of Thomas Fireheart's plans to take over the Daily Bugle

results.title: Flesh and Blood
results.description: Spider-Man and Rocket Racer search for Skinhead

results.title: Rematch
results.description: The Grizzly wants a rematch with Spider-Man

results.title: With Great Power
results.description: Doctor Doom sends Titania against the cosmic-powered Spider-Man

results.title: Gold Rush!
results.description: Spider-Man, caught in the aftermath of the Beyonder turning an office building into solid gold, takes a gold notebook for himself

results.title: The Harder They Fall
results.description: The triumvirate of Doctor Doom, the Kingpin and Magneto sends Goliath against the cosmic-powered Spider-Man

results.title: Dragon in the Dark
results.description: The villains responsible for the Acts of Vengeance send the Dragon Man after the cosmic-powered Spider-Man

results.title: All That Glitters ...
results.description: The Molten Man is paroled from prison and comes to visit his step-sister, Liz Allan Osborn

results.title: Clouds from a Distant Storm
results.description: Mister Fear uses Betty Brant Leeds to lure Spider-Man into a trap

results.title: Once More, with Feeling
results.description: The Chameleon assembles the villains defeated by Spider-Man during the Acts of Vengeance and offers them each $100,000 to kill the wall-crawler; Peter Parker loses his job at the Daily Bugle

results.title: The Last Act of Vengeance
results.description: The Chameleon double-crosses his hired guns after they apparently succeed in killing Spider-Man

results.title: Friends and Enemies
results.description: Spider-Man teams with the Green Goblin and the Molten Man to stop Tombstone's robbery of Osborn Chemicals

results.title: With Friends Like These!
results.description: Spider-Man confronts Harry Osborn about his continued use of the Green Goblin identity; Tombstone finds that he is nearly indestructible following his exposure to an experimental gas

results.title: Tombstone Territory
results.description: Spider-Man and Robbie Robertson intervene as Tombstone makes a play for Hammerhead's mob

results.title: A Subtle Shade of Green
results.description: Spider-Man discovers the Hulk in Connecticut and is accidentally dosed with gamma radiation

results.title: Welcome ... to My Nightmare!
results.description: Nightmare enlisted the aid of Spider-Man's subconscious mind to stop a dream manifestation of the Hulk

results.title: A Hulk by Any Other Name ...
results.description: Spider-Man briefly transforms into a Spider-Hulk

results.title: Fortune's Fury
results.description: Spider-Man, Dominic Fortune and Silver Sable close in on ex-Nazi Simon Steele; Fortune discovers that his old flame Sabbath Raven is alive and married to Steele

results.title: The Reckoning
results.description: Spider-Man, Dominic Fortune and Silver Sable close in on ex-Nazi Simon Steele; Fortune is finally reunited with Sabbath Raven

results.title: Head Quest (Art Attack, Part 1)
results.description: The Headmen, searching for Spider-Man, crash the opening of Alicia Masters Storm's art exhibit

results.title: Art and Soul (Art Attack, Part 2)
results.description: The Painter sends Spark against Spider-Man as a prelude to his masterpiece:  a new ice age for New York City

results.title: Cold Hands Warm Art (Art Attack, Part 3)
results.description: The Avant Guard unleashes a blizzard which even the combined might of New York City's heroes cannot contain

results.title: Art's Desire! (Art Attack, Part 4)
results.description: Spider-Man and the Human Torch confront the Avant Guard and learn the secret of the Painter

results.title: Home Is Where the Terror Is!
results.description: A charity ball is disrupted by a group of Morlocks, then crashed by the new Firebrand

results.title: Toast of the Town ...
results.description: As the supporting cast crawls from the wreckage of the collapsed building, Cloak and Dagger fight the man responsible (Firebrand), and Spider-Man helps a group of Morlocks in the sewers below

results.title: First Blood ...
results.description: Silvermane sends a squad of android mercenaries to kidnap Spider-Man

results.title: Local Superhero!
results.description: Peter Parker is sent by the Daily Bugle to a small town in Pennsylvania to uncover the mystery of the Smithville Thunderbolt

results.title: This Blood Is My Blood
results.description: Silvermane needs Spider-Man's blood to keep him alive, but the Black Cat has other ideas

results.title: Living in Fear
results.description: A super-powered drug runner, in attempting to force his brother to steal $1,000,000 in negotiable securities, sees an opportunity for revenge against Spider-Man

results.title: Pumping Up!
results.description: Man-Mountain Marko resorts to steroids to prepare him for his rematch with Spider-Man
